INDONESIAN POLITICAL COUNSELOR SINGGIH CONFIRMED "UNOFFICIALLY" TO EMBOFF ON APRIL 14 THAT IVAN SHPED'KO, CHIEF OF THE SOVIET MFS'S SECOND FAR EAST DIVISION (JAPAN, PHILIPPINES, INDONESIA) WOULD BE NAMED AMBASSADOR TO INDONESIA.
SINGGIH WAS NOT SPECIFIC ABOUT THE EXPECTED TIMING OF THIS SHIFT, BUT THOUGHT IT WOULD BE FAIRLY SOON.
SHPED'KO'S POSITION WOULD BE POSSIBILITY FOR OLEG TROYANOVSKIY, WHO IS RETURNING SOON FROM OVER NINE YEARS AS SOVIET AMBASSADOR TO JAPAN.
BREMENT ']
DURING THE PARLIAMENTARY DEBATE ON THE EXPANDED ROLE OF STATE-OWNED BRITISH NATIONAL OIL COMPANY (BNOC) ACCORDED BY SUBJECT CHANGES, CONSERVATIVES OBJECTED TO BNOC'S SPECIAL PRIVILEGES.

CONSERVATIVE "SHADOW" ENERGY MINISTER TOM KING SAID THE ANNOUNCEMENTS REPORTED IN REFTEL (A) FLY "IN THE FACE OF ALL THE ASSURANCES GIVEN BY GOVERNMENT MINISTERS AT THE TIME OF THE READING OF TH (1975) PETROLEUM AND SUBMARINE PIPELINES BILL THAT BNOC WOULD NOT BE GIVEN SPECIAL PRIVILEGES...
WE ALSO REGARD IT AS CLOSE TO AN ABUSE OF MINISTERIAL ADMINISTRATIVE POWER TO GIVE A PRE-EMPTIVE RIGHT IN FARM-INS AS A FIRST OPTION, WHICH WAS NOT INCLUDED IN THE LEGISLATION."
KING SAID, "WE REGARD IT AS ESSENTIAL TO HAVE CONFIDENCE AND TRUST IN THE FAIR DEALINGS OF THE BRITISH GOVERN- MENT... (AND)
REGARD (ENERGY SECRETARY BENN'S ANNOUNCE- MENT) AS NOT HELPFUL IN THAT DIRECTION."

ANOTHER CONSERVATIVE MEMBER OF PARLIAMENT TERMED THE ANNOUNCEMENTS "A MAJOR STEP TOWARDS FURTHER BACK DOOR NATIONALIZATION" AND "A BREACH OF UNDERTAKINGS" GIVEN TH HOUSE OF COMMONS AND INDUSTRY AND SAID THEY "WILL DO NOTHING TO IMPROVE THE PROSPECTS OF MORE EFFICIENT PRODUCTION OF THIS OIL OR IMPROVE THE TAKE THE BRITISH PEOPLE WILL GET FROM IT." 3.

LABOR MEMBERS OF PARLIAMENT WHO SUPPORTED THE ANNOUNCEMENTS TENDED TO EQUATE BNOC'S ROLE WITH BRITISH CONTROL OF THE OIL, WHILE CONSERVATIVES HELD THAT THE U.K. ALREADY HAS FULL AUTHORITY OVER ALL OIL ON THE CONTINENTAL SHELF. 4.

SECRETARY BENN GAVE THE FOLLOWING POSSIBLE CLUE TO FUTURE DEPLETION POLICIES: "AT PRESENT WE ARE MOVING FROM NO OIL THREE YEARS AGO TO 60 MILLION TONNES THIS YEAR AND POSSIBLY 150 MILLION TONNES BY THE MID-1980S ON THE BASIS OF FIELDS ALREADY UNDER DEVELOPMENT.
THE RATIONAL AND SENSIBLE THING TO DO IS TO RETAIN DISCRETIO OVER DEPLETION POLICY
SO THAT WE CAN PUSH THE GAINS FROM THE NORTH SEA FURTHER INTO THE FUTURE INSTEAD OF BEING PRESSED BY COMMERCIAL CONSIDERATIONS WHICH WOULD HAPPEN IF WE DEPENDED ENTIRELY ON THE PRIVATE SECTOR."
BREWSTER ']
['SOUTH ASIAN NUCLEAR PROPOSAL 1.

(LOU) INDIAN PAPERS MAY 28 GAVE PROMINENT COVERAGE TO ACCOUNTS FILED BY THEIR CORRESPONDENTS IN THE U.S. OF THE NEW YORK TIMES STORY REPORTING A USG PROPOSAL FOR A SOUTH ASIAN NUCLEAR WEAPONS FREE ZONE GUARANTEED BY THE U.S., THE SOVIET UNION, AND THE PRC.
MAY 29 PRESS STORIES DATELINED NEW DELHI INDICATE THAT THE GOI HAS MOVED SMARTLY TO SHOOT DOWN THE REPORTED INITIATIVE.
WE UNDERSTAND THAT MEA SPOKESMAN PURUSHOTTAM WAS THE PRIME MOVER IN THE OPERATION.
(U) THESE STORIES DIFFER SOMEWHAT, BUT THEY ALL CARRY THE BASIC THEME THAT THE PROPOSAL IS UNACCEPTABLE TO INDIA.
THE INDIAN EXPRESS REPORTS THAT "WHILE NEW DELHI WITHHELD ITS OFFICIAL COMMENT ON THE REPORTED U.S. MOVES..., INFORMAL SOUNDINGS HERE SHOWED THAT INDIA WILL OUTRIGHTLY REJECT THE MOVE."

THE EXPRESS ACCOUNT ADDS THE FAMILIAR LINE THAT "INDIA HAS MADE IT CLEAR MORE THAN ONCE THAT WHILE IT DOES NOT WANT TO GO IN FOR NUCLEAR WEAPONS, IT CANNOT ACCEPT TWO SETS OF STANDARDS--ONE FOR THE NUCLEAR HAVES AND THE OTHER FOR THE NUCLEAR HAVE-NOTS.
THE NUCLEAR FREE ZONE PROPOSAL IN ESSENCE UNDERSCORES THE DISCRIMINATORY PRIN- CIPLE WHICH INDIA DISAPPROVES OF.
NEW DELHI ALSO DOES NOT APPROVE OF A NUCLEAR FREE ZONE IN ASIA WHICH DOES NOT INCLUDE CHINA." 3.
(U) THE TIMES OF INDIA SAYS THE REPORTED U.S. MOVE "IS SEEN HERE
AS A DUBIOUS PLOY TO IGNORE THE UNILATERAL DECLARATION ALREADY MADE BY THIS COUNTRY AND TO CONTINUE TO MAINTAIN AN ARTIFICIAL PARITY BETWEEN INDIA AND PAKISTAN."
THE TOI ADDS THAT "TWENTY YEARS OF MILITARY BALANCE TILTED AGAINST INDIA IS NOW BEING..PURSUED BY THE U.S.A. IN THE NUCLEAR FIELD AS WELL."
ACCORDING TO THE TIMES, THE PROPOSAL IS "BLATANTLY DISCRIMINATORY" IN THAT IT WILL MAKE CHINA MORE EQUAL THAN THE REST OF THE ASIAN COUNTRIES." 4.
THE STATESMAN SAYS THAT THE PROPOSAL "IF ITS AUTHORS ARE SERIOUSLY PLANNING TO SET IT AFLOAT, WILL BE REJECTED OUT OF HAND BY THIS COUNTRY ACCORDING TO INFORMED SOURCES"

ACCORDING TO THE STATESMAN, THE SOURCES REITERATED THE GOI VIEW THAT WHILE INDIA HAS UNILATERALLY DECIDED AGAINST BUILDING A NUCLEAR WEAPONS CAPABILITY SHE WOULD NOT GRANT THE NUCLEAR WEAPONS POWERS THE RIGHT TO DICTATE TO OTHERS WHAT TO DO AND NOT TO DO.

COMPLAINING ABOUT THE PROPOSAL "CONFERRING SUPER-POWER STATUS ON CHINA," THE STATESMAN ACCOUNT NOTES THAT "ANYTHING THAT EVEN REMOTELY SMACKS OF BEING DISCRIMINATORY WOULD BE TOTALLY UNACCEPTABLE TO THE GOI."
IT ADDS THAT "THE PROVISION OF INTERNATIONAL IN- SPECTION AND SAFEGUARDS TOO WOULD NOT BE ACCEPTABLE TO INDIA AS LONG
AS
THE BIG POWERS TO DID NOT AGREE TO SIMILAR SAFEGUARDS AND SUPERVISION." 5.
(LOU)
THE INDIAN EMBASSY IN WASHINGTON MAY ALSO BE INVOLVED IN SHOOTING DOWN THE REPORTED PROPOSAL.
WE NOTE AN ARTICLE IN THE MAY 28 HINDU FILED BY ITS WASH- INGTON CORRESPONDENT N. RAVI IN WHICH HE WRITES THAT "EVEN WITH NUCLEAR GUARANTEES, A SANWFZ WOULD NOT BE ACCEPTABLE IN THAT FORM TO INDIA.
RAVI CITES TWO BASIC INDIAN OBJECTIONS:

THE CREATION OF SUCH A ZONE WOULD BE DISCRIMINATORY AGAINST THE NNWSS AND "THE VERY IDEA OF A SECURITY GUARANTEE THE POLICING OF THE U.S., THE SOVIET UNION, AND CHINA WOULD SIGNIFY A SUPERIOR-INFERIOR RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN THE THREE GUARANTOR NATIONS AND THE COUNTRIES OF THE REGION." 6.
(U) JANATA MP SUBRAMANIAM SWAMY HAS ALSO CHIMED IN.

CALLING THE PROPOSAL "MISCHIEVOUS" AND "FRAUDULENT", SWAMY MAKES THE FAMILIAR ALLEGATION THAT THE U.S. HAS BLOWN THE GROWING NUCLEAR CAPABILITY OF PAKISTAN OUT OF ALL PROPORATIONS TO SCARE INDIA INTO A SAFEGUARDS AGREE-MENT.

JAYASINGHE SAID FONSEKA'S INSTRUCTIONS WERE SUFFICIENTLY FLEXIBLE TO ENABLE HIM TO WORK WITH USDEL TO TRY AND ARRIVE AT GENERALLY ACCEPTABLE CONCLUSION.
HE HOPED THIS WOULD BE POSSIBLE, BUT DECLINED TO BE MORE SPECIFIC.
COMMENT: WE ARE INCLINED TO ACCEPT JAYASINGHE'S STATEMENT AT FACE VALUE.
GSL DELEGATIONS TO INTERNATIONAL MEETINGS ARE ORDINARILY INSTRUCTED TO GENERALLY GET THE BEST DEAL POSSIBLE FOR LDC'S WITHOUT MUCH SPECIFIC GUIDANCE.
WE WOULD EXPECT FONSEKA TO BE AS COOPERATIVE AS POSSIBLE WITHIN THE LDC CON- SENSUS.

SANTIAGO DECLARED IN STATE OF EMERGENCY
THE CHILEAN GOVERNMENT HAS DECLARED A STATE OF EMERGENCY IN SANTIAGO PROVINCE FOLLOWING A CONFUSED INCIDENT INVOLVING ARMY COMMANDER- IN- CHIEF PRATS.
AFTER WHAT WAS EITHER AN ATTEMPT AGAINST PRATS' LIFE OR AN ASSAULT ON A LADY DRIVER BY PRATS, THE GENERAL TENDERED HIS RESIGNATION, WHICH ALLENDE REFUSED.
IT WAS ALSO REPORTED THAT A COUP ATTEMPT HAD BEEN FRUSTRATED WITH THE ARREST OF AN UNDISCLOSED NUMBER OF MILITARY AND CIVILIAN PLOTTERS.
( CONFIDENTIAL) SANTIAGO 2813 AND 2829, USDAO/ SANTIAGO 281605 Z JUN, 6/28. 2.

FEDAYEEN OPPOSE PALESTINIAN STATE PROPOSAL EMBASSY BEIRUT REPORTS THAT THE IDEA OF A PALESTINIAN STATE ADVANCED BY EGYPT AND TUNISIA IS DRAWING IN- CREASING OPPOSITION FROM ALL FEDAYEEN ORGANIZATIONS.
OUR EMBASSY COMMENTS THAT MORE REASONABLE AND MODERATE FEDAYEEN LEADERS WERE APPARENTLY IN TACIT AGREEMENT WITH THE IDEA, BUT EXTREMISTS HAVE FORCED THEM TO COME OUT AGAINST IT.
( LIMITED OFFICIAL USE)
JAPANESE WORRIED ABOUT SOYBEANS
THE JAPANESE FOREIGN OFFICE HAS EXPRESSED TO EMBASSY TOKYO ITS CONCERN OVER THE IMPLICATIONS OF THE US AGRICULTURAL EXPORT EMBARGO.

THE JAPANESE INTEND TO RAISE THE QUESTION OF US RELIABILITY AS AN AGRICULTURAL SUPPLIER AT THE JULY 16-17 MINISTERIAL MEETING, AND OUR EMBASSY RECORDS INCREASING TALK IN JAPAN OF THE NEED TO DIVERSIFY AGRICULTURAL SUPPLY SOURCES AS WELL AS INCREASE SELF- SUFFICIENCY.
( CONFIDENTIAL) TOKYO 8165, 6/28. 4.

THE REQUIREMENT FOR MONTHLY ECONOMIC TRENDS REPORTING, INCLUDING EXTENSIVE STATISTICAL DATA, FROM THE SMALLER OECD COUNTRIES.
THE EMBASSY BELIEVES A REPORT OF THIS TYPE WILL SERVE A USEFUL PURPOSE, BUT WOULD LIKE SOME CLARIFICATION CONCERNING THE STATISTICAL INPUT.
(A) ARE THE EXTENSIVE STATISTICS OUTLINED IN MR.
GOODMAN'S MEMORANDUM TO POSTS IN NORTHERN EUROPE NEEDED FOR NEW ZEALAND AS WELL?
WE NOTE IN THIS REGARD THAT REF.
A WAS NOT CLEARED IN EITHER EUR/RPE OR IN THE EA BUREAU (EA/ANZ OR EA/EP), AND ASSUME THAT THE M/MO/R APPROVAL OBVIATES REGIONAL NEED FOR REGIONAL CLEARANCE.
THE EMBASSY IS ALREADY REPORTING NEARLY ALL THE REQUESTED DATA SEMI-ANNUALLY IN THE ECONOMIC TRENDS REPORT,AND SUBMITTING AS WELL ALL OF THE STATISTICAL DATA REQUESTED IN REF
A AS IT BECOMES AVAILABLE AS PART OF THE CERP PUBLICATIONS PROGRAM (WHETHER WEEKLY, MONTHLY OR QUARTERLY).
IS THE NEW REQUIREMENT OF SUCH HIGH PRIORITY THAT DUPLICATION BECOMES ESSENTIAL?

(C) WOULD INTERESTED END USERS FIND IT SATISFACTORY FOR THE POST TO SUBMIT A BRIEF SUMMARY OF ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENTS FOR THE MONTH, CITING ONLY THOSE STATISTICS RELEVANT TO SPECIFIC MONTHLY KEY ISSUES?
SUCH, WE BELIEVE,COULD BE USEFUL AND STILL AVOID THE DUPLICATIVE REPORTING THAT THE ORIGINAL FORMAT WOULD REQUIRE.
ANSWERS TO THE POINTS RAISED WILL BE HELPFUL TO THE EMBASSY IN ADJUSTING ITS VOLUNTARY REPORTING PLANS IN ORDER TO ALLOW FOR THIS NEW REQUIREMENT.

THE SWEDISH DELEGATION TO THE INTER-AMERICAN DEVELOPMENT BANK ANNUAL MEETING IN VANCOUVER, APRIL 17-19, WILL BE LED BY JOHAN NORDENFALK, UNDER SECRETARY OF THE MINISTRY OF COMMERCE, AND WILL INCLUDE, FROM STOCKHOLM, CAROLINE FLEETWOOD OF THE MINISTRY OF FOREIGN AFFAIRS AND BJORN SKALA OF THE MINISTRY FOR INTERNATIONAL DEVELOPMENT COOPERATION, AND, FROM WASH- INGTON, ULF DINKELSPIEL OF THE SWEDISH EMBASSY.
entities: UNDER SECRETARY OF THE MINISTRY OF COMMERCE

content: ALSO, THE SWEDISH DELEGATION WILL INCLUDE KARL WARNBERG, HEAD OF THE SWEDISH EXPORT COUNCIL, AMBASSADOR GORAN ENGBLOM, SWEDISH AMBASSADOR TO PERU, AND REPRESENTATIVES OF THE SWEDISH INDUS- TRIAL FEDERATION, THE SWEDISH BUILDING CONTRACTORS, SWEDISH BANKERS ASSOCIATION, AND PROBABLY OTHERS.
(SOME OF THESE PERSONAGES WILL BE IN SAN FRANCISCO BEFORE THE VANCOUVER MEETING, FOR A "SEMINAR ON ALASKA", ORGANIZED BY THE SWEDISH CONSULATE GENERAL.
THEY PROCEED TO VANCOUVER ON SATURDAY, APRIL 15.) 2.
NORDENFALK WOULD LIKE TO MEET WITH ASSISTANT SECRETARY BERGSTEN TO DISCUSS (1) HUMAN RIGHTS CONSIDERATIONS IN THE IDB; (2) PROTECTIONISM; (3) TRANSFER OF TECHNOLOGY.
COMMENT: THE PARTICIPATION OF REPRESENTATIVES FROM INDUS- TRY, BANKING, ETC., ILLUSTRATES SWEDEN'S INTEREST IN DEVELOP- ING TRADE AND INVESTMENT THROUGH ITS NEW MEMBERSHIP IN THE IDB.

THE FACT THAT THE MINISTRY OF COMMERCE FUNDED SWEDEN'S IDB MEMBERSHIP, RATHER THAN THE DEVELOPMENT COOPERATION MINISTRY, HAS PERMITTED THE GOS TO ACCENTUATE TRADE--AND EMPLOYMENT IN SWEDEN--THROUGH THE IDB, I.E., THROUGH CONTRACTS WHICH THE IDB MIGHT FUND.
AMBASSADOR ENGBLOM PREPARED A SPECIAL SUTDY IN 1977 ON INTEGRATING SWEDISH INDUSTRIES MORE CLOSELY WITH SWEDISH FOREIGN AID AND HE CAN BE EXPECTED TO BE AN ACTIVE MEMBER OF THE SWEDISH TEAM.
KENNEDY-MINOTT ']
